\n<Wanz>Katara, it's been quite a while since we came here. I
thought this town was kind of unpleasant at first, but you
get used to it, huh-

\n<Katara>I was worried someone from home might come and find us, but

\n<Katara>I thought maybe pursuers from home would come, but it looks

\n<Katara>Geez! Grandpa!?
\n<Grandpa>Phew... I've finally found you. Young master. Young lady.
1ルイ困惑
\n<Louie>...that's the situation. Grandpa, do you understand?
1ワンズ困惑
\n<Wanz>...that's how it is. Sorry, Grandpa. Do you understand?

\n<Grandpa>Hmm. Well, it's mostly as I expected. I understand the
feelings of both the young master and young lady. I have no
intention of taking you back immediately. Please be at ease.

\n<Grandpa>Let's have a little talk about the history of the Catfield
family. And the real reason why Miss Chelsea was expelled
from the house.

\n<Grandpa>Long ago, "humans" and "beastmen" were clearly
distinguished. It was a time when humans treated beastmen as
slaves. You know this from your lessons.

\n<Grandpa>Compared to humans, beastmen often have superior physical
abilities. Yet, why were they treated as slaves... The
reason is simple. Humans were numerous and united.

\n<Grandpa>On the other hand, beastmen have various roots in their
ancestry. Cats, dogs, raccoons, rabbits, foxes, and so on...
It's natural that they weren't united.

\n<Grandpa>The majority, being humans, discriminated against beastmen,
scorned them, and made them serve. There was such an era.
But now, that is no longer the case.

\n<Grandpa>The first head of the Catfield family united the scattered
beastmen and stood up for the rights of beastmen together.
Regardless of being cats or dogs, they rose up to demand
rights for all beastmen.

\n<Grandpa>After many years, humans and beastmen reconciled. Humans and
beastmen are equals and good friends.

\n<Grandpa>Now beastmen are treated as humans too. You two may not feel
it much since you were born in an era where this is normal.

\n<Grandpa>However, this is where the problem starts. After the
discrimination against beastmen disappeared. I'm talking
about events that are happening right now.

\n<Grandpa>What happens when discrimination disappears? When a negative
becomes zero, it doesn't end there. With that momentum, it
moves from zero to positive.

\C[14]\n<Grandpa>"Beastmen are special"\C[0]. After being oppressed for so
long, they should be favored now. That's how the ideology
shifted.

\n<Grandpa>The current head of the family... your father has become
what is called "beastmen supremacism". The belief that
beastmen are superior to humans.

\n<Grandpa>Miss Chelsea has always been fair to everyone. Whether human
or beastman, she treated everyone equally and fought with
them fairly. She fought equally and made up equally.

\n<Grandpa>And before you knew it, there were many smiles around Miss
Chelsea. She had such a mysterious charm. She didn't care at
all whether someone was human or beastman.

\n<Grandpa>That was something the head of the family could not
tolerate. "Being equal to humans", that was considered "a
disgrace to the Catfield family".
1ルイ困惑
\n<Louie>Why did you tell us this now, Grandpa?
1ワンズ困惑
\n<Wanz>Why are you telling us this now, Grandpa?

\n<Grandpa>I have served the Catfield family for generations. However,
I do not believe that the current head's views are correct.

\n<Grandpa>If you two lived surrounded by beastmen in that house
without any inconvenience, surely you would adopt the same
ideology as the head of the family.

\n<Grandpa>This is also a good opportunity. I thought it might be good
for you to continue your social studies for a while longer.
In exchange, I will stay as well.
